26/12/2002
ATHENS, Greece -- The Bank of Greece and the National Bank of Yugoslavia are to sign a co-operation memorandum Friday (27 December), which includes an exchange of information and support for Yugoslav authorities trying to meet their monetary policy goals.
Greece has already signed agreements with Bulgaria and Albania, and is considering similar commitments with the central banks of Romania and Turkey.
Greek banks have expanded rapidly in the region over the past few years and currently have representatives in all countries in Southeast Europe.
(Macedonian Press Agency - 24/12/02)
